<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06217247 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06217247 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  TOKYO; MOVIE; FESTIVAL  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  THE TOKYO International Film Festival launches its fourth installment Sept.27-Oct. 6, featuring an international competition of 14 films and asubstantial lineup of Hollywood studio and independent films.;    At a newsconference this past week in Tokyo, Isao Matsuoka, chairman of the publicitycommittee of the Tokyo fest and president of Toho Co. Ltd., reported that morethan 140 films would be screened at the festival and said he expected recordattendance from overseas. Last year's festival brought about 500 producers,distributors, film makers and executives from abroad.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Arts andamp; Books  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TOKYO FESTIVAL TO SCREEN 140 FILMS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Film  </MEMO><TEXT>     Opening the festival's slate of special invitational films is Japan's&quot;Father and Son&quot; (tentative title), directed by Yoji Yamada and starringRetaro Mikuni.;    Among the festival's most eagerly awaited screenings willbe the invitational's closing film, Wim Wenders' epic &quot;Until the End of theWorld,&quot; starring William Hurt.;    U.S. films screening during theinvitational include &quot;Regarding Henry,&quot; &quot;City Slickers,&quot; Istvan Szabo's&quot;Meeting Venus,&quot; Mel Brooks' &quot;Life Stinks,&quot; John Singleton's &quot;Boyz N the Hood&quot;and Wolfgang Petersen's &quot;Shattered.&quot;;    Also screening will be ToshioMasuda's &quot;Edojyo Tairan&quot; and Kazuki Omori's &quot;Godzilla vs. King Ghidora,&quot; bothfrom Japan.;    Two films will be screened in homage to directors AkiraKurosawa and Satyajit Ray: &quot;The Seven Samurai&quot; and &quot;The Stranger,&quot;respectively.;    Additionally, 14 films are in the process of being selectedfor the international competition from 168 entries representing 39 countries.Jury chairman Lewis Gilbert, the director of &quot;Shirley Valentine&quot; and theupcoming &quot;Stepping Out,&quot; presides over the seven jury members who will selectthe Tokyo Grand Prix, the special jury prize and other prizes.;    Jurymembers, as well as the names of the features, are expected to be announced bythe end of August.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Hollywood Reporter  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910804  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  29  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  281  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday August 4, 199100217247,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>